---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for Multi-Brand Portfolios in 2026';
const description = 'A practical guide to Shopify email apps for multi-brand portfolios, covering account separation, shared reporting, segmentation, pricing context, citations, and tradeoffs.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Portfolios needing deep brand-level segmentation','Rich events and configurable customer profiles','Governance and account structure require planning','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Retail groups coordinating campaigns across brands','Accessible email and SMS automation','Brand-specific exceptions require QA','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Sequenzy','Small operators managing focused brand sequences','Simple repeatable workflows','Limited portfolio-level complexity should be checked','https://sequenzy.io/'],['Brevo','Portfolios combining lifecycle and transactional email','Broad messaging toolkit','More manual separation and reporting','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Drip','DTC groups comparing repeat purchase by brand','Commerce automation and reporting','Less appropriate for mixed non-commerce portfolios','https://www.drip.com/features']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">A multi-brand operator needs economies of scale without accidental cross-brand messaging. The platform should make separation, permissions, sender identity, consent, and reporting visible to the team.</p><p>We prioritize brand isolation, reusable patterns, portfolio-level learning, and clean ownership. Confirm current account, seat, and billing structures from official documentation before consolidating stores.</p><h2>Shortlist by portfolio need</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>First workflow</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[0]==='Klaviyo'?'Brand-specific lifecycle':a[0]==='Omnisend'?'Shared campaign framework':a[0]==='Sequenzy'?'Brand onboarding sequence':a[0]==='Brevo'?'Cross-brand transactional standard':'Portfolio retention report'}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for multi-brand portfolios</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[0]} should make it difficult to confuse audiences, domains, product catalogs, or sender identities. Centralize what is genuinely shared—QA, naming, and reporting—while keeping each brand’s consent and content rules explicit.</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[2]}. Build one brand first, document the reusable pieces, and add the next store only after checking data separation and deliverability. Portfolio-level findings should be reported as evidence from comparable cohorts, not as a universal performance promise.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}; supports a controlled multi-brand rollout; can use Shopify data.</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}; accounts, seats, and contact volume affect cost.</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Verify official plans for brands, contacts, sends, seats, and SMS.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Portfolio priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Deep brand-level event logic</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible profiles and segments.</td></tr><tr><td>Lean repeated sequences</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Focused workflows reduce maintenance.</td></tr><tr><td>Brand-level repeat-purchase analysis</td><td>Drip</td><td>Commerce reporting orientation.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Continue with the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/guides/deliverability">deliverability guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
